            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> Caesar divi Traiani Part<supplied reason="lost">hici <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ilius</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="2"/>divi Nerv<supplied reason="lost">ae</supplied> <expan><abbr>n</abbr><ex>epos</ex></expan> Traianus Hadrianus <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustus</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>pont</abbr><ex>ifex</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr><supplied reason="lost">tr</supplied>ib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> IIII co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> III <lb n="4"/>aquae aeternitati consuluit <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>Q</abbr><ex>uintus</ex></expan> Servilius Candidus pecunia sua perduxit
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Text and support identical with IRT 358a; text carved on the flat rear. Text duplicated in IRT 359. Reused as building material in the stage.</p>
            </div>
